title: Karen Olguin
text:
Business Analytics Student | Summer Analyst | Quality Assurance Auditor

karenolguinliz@gmail.com | linkedin.com/in/karenolguinl | 208.973.8558



September 2021 - April 2025
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID
- Bachelor of Science in Business Analytics
- Minors: Finance, Financial Planning
- Scholarship: Brigham Young University - Idaho Academic Grant (2021 - 2024)
- Tools: Power BI, Python, Excel, Alteryx, Tableau, MySQL, RStudio



June - August 2024
Goldman Sachs, Salt Lake City, UT
Summer Analyst, Operations - PWM
- Automated trade booking process using Alteryx and Tableau, saving 1.5 hours daily and reducing manual errors.
- Implemented JIRA frameworks to improve workload visibility, progress tracking, and deadlines.
- Streamlined homepage resources, reducing tool search time by 30%.
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID
IT Quality Assurance Auditor
- Audited analysts’ work and provided feedback, improving process quality from 92% to 97%.
- Delivered bi-weekly training sessions to enhance technical and customer service skills.
IT Analyst
- Resolved technical needs for 23+ users daily via phone, email, and chat using tools like Team Dynamix, Zoom, and Zoho Assist.
- Solved over 700 incidents related to technological errors and service requests.



July 2018 - September 2020
The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, Mexico City, Mexico
Full-time Volunteer Representative
- Examined team statistics to improve training meetings and teaching methods.
- Increased service request efficiency from 25% to 36% by creating Excel report models and forecasting future needs.



Quality Student Consultant (July 2023)
- Analyzed employee performance using Power BI charts in bi-weekly reports to generate key insights and improve analysts’ productivity.
